<p><a href="#sdfootnote19anc" name="sdfootnote19sym">19</a>Geoengineering refers to deliberate, large-scale intervention in the climate system designed to counter climate change or offset some of its effects. It is commonly divided into three broad classes: carbon dioxide removal, solar radiation management and Earth radiation management technologies. For more see Clive Hamilton, <em>Earthmasters: The Dawn of the Age of Climate Engineering</em> (Yale University Press, 2014); <a href="http://www.geoengineeringmonitor.org/what-is-geoengineering/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">http://www.geoengineeringmonitor.org/what-is-geoengineering/</a>.</p>
