<p><a href="#sdfootnote79anc" name="sdfootnote79sym">79</a>Ursula Biemann, ‘Egyptian Chemistry’ in Benthônico, <em>Provisões: Uma Conferência Visual [World of Matter]</em>, 31–35.</p>
<p><a href="#sdfootnote80anc" name="sdfootnote80sym">80</a>The relation to ‘hybrids’ – the construction of systems that mix politics, science, technology, and nature – has been theorised in Latour, <em>We Have Never Been Modern</em>.</p>
